doctype html
html
  head
    title Shop Demo
    meta(name='viewport' content='width=device-width, initial-scale=1')
    style.
      * {box-sizing: border-box;}
      body {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
      }
      .topnav {
      overflow: hidden;
      background-color: #e9e9e9;
      }
      .topnav a {
      float: left;
      display: block;
      color: black;
      text-align: center;
      padding: 14px 16px;
      text-decoration: none;
      font-size: 17px;
      }
      .topnav a:hover {
      background-color: #ddd;
      color: black;
      }
      .topnav a.active {
      background-color: #2196F3;
      color: white;
      }
      .topnav input[type=text] {
      float: right;
      padding: 6px;
      margin-top: 8px;
      margin-right: 16px;
      border: none;
      font-size: 17px;
      }
  body
    .topnav
      a.active(href='#{home}') Home
      a(href='#{users}') Users
      a(href='#{addUser}') Add User
    div(style='padding-left:16px')
      h2 This is my home project shop-demo
      p This front-end using Jade engine with Express JS Framework 
      p This project has 3 tabs for 3 different function
      p Besides this project has 2 routes API are
      p - /shop-demo/api/user (get/post) (get for list and post for add more user)
      p - /shop-demo/search/:string (string is name you want to search).
      p All this API routes have Basic Authenticate with encode base64 signature (username: test, password: 123456) 
      p you can use Postman for all this api routes.
